blog.name: autonomy1
blog.title: Peter Percival-AUTONOMY
blog.description: Shades, nuances, scraps of existence......looking directly at an object can sometimes be a meaningless, even a destructive use of time…in society we are trained to look at things quickly, process that information and move on to another view…so much information and meaning can be lost in the action of moving on….by changing the expected angle of view, or re-arranging elements of an image one can derive another meaning from it, and if not an absolute meaning an abstract one which makes us look once again…that is all one can ask for, another look…(©) Pete Percival - 2013 All Rights Reserved. Reproduction of any kind is illegal.

summary: A drunk bistro passerby patron once growled at me that Art isn't art until someone gets naked.  All I could think to say was,...
body:
A drunk bistro passerby patron once growled at me that Art isn’t art until someone gets naked.  All I could think to say was, “They have no instruments to measure that.”  To which he said his instrument measures that.  He probably meant his dick but in my heart of hearts I wanted him to pull out some Men In Black Industrial Light and Magic shit, some bizarre metal probing alien stuff that measures art’s worth.

Here now are some things that I’ve painted since

summary: This one is done!   Devil Gundam Ver. NXS.  My own take on the notorious mobile suit in Mobile Fighter G Gundam, a show run on...
caption:
This one is done!   Devil Gundam Ver. NXS.  My own take on the notorious mobile suit in Mobile Fighter G Gundam, a show run on ham and testosterone lmao.   As a kid the Devil Gundam (Dark Gundam as it is known in the US) always sent a chill down my spine whenever it appeared.  Whenever I heard that theme that played I knew shit was about to get real <_> 


Currently working on turning this into a shirt!   I’ve ordered a test product so I can see how it will look.  If I think it looks good I’ll post a link up to it, for right now enjoy the image!

Each image was sketched out in Clip Studio Paint EX, then brought over to Adobe Illustrator for inking and compositing.  The damn program crashed a lot on me when I was making the collage <_>
